args: Bad news, guys! A carriage fell off\na cliff on a mountain pass!
One of 'em is still alive, but barely.\nWe're bringin' him in right now.\n...Cleo! We need ya over here!
...I have done what I can. I fear the rest\ncomes down to the strength of your will.
I appreciate the help, but...\nI can handle the truth.
It's too late for me, isn't it?\nIt's okay. I'm not afraid to die.
Y-you mustn't talk like that!\nHere, try to eat something.
But if you don't eat, you'll die!
You can't just give up on life like this!\nI won't LET you give up!
I'm gonna give you the will to live!
So, um...can I ask why you\naren't afraid of dying?
My girlfriend was in the carriage with me.
There's no meaning to living in a world\nwhere she no longer exists.
Besides, if I die, I might see her again.\nSo that's why I'm not scared.
But if you die, you can't take it back!\nYou can't do anything ever again!
You'll never experience fun or happiness\never again. Or joy, or love, or anything!\nYou need to live. I WANT you to live!
So if you don't mind, I'm just gonna sit\nhere and talk to you for a while. Okay?
Okay! So whenever I eat good food,\nI always feel happy to be alive.
Food means nothing if she's not\nthere to share it with me.
What about happy times? Or fun times?\nDon't you remember those?
Our first vacation together was fun.
She was so pure and honest...\nYou actually remind me of her a little.
What was she like? Tell me about her!\nTell me her hopes and dreams and stuff.
Heh. Well, there was this one thing\nshe always mentioned...
Well, it's a little thing, but she always\nwanted to open up a restaurant in\nsome peaceful little village.

She loved cooking, and she thought we
could run the place together. ...Heh.
She always got this dopey look on her
face whenever she talked about it.
But none of this matters now. She's gone.
She told you about that dream,\nwhich also makes it yours.
So as long as you're alive, you can make\nit come trueâ€”for her AND for you.
Do you...do you really think so?
Of course I do! There's nothing better in\nthe world than making a dream come true.\nIt's just the happiest thing there is.
So you need to work on that dream and\nkeep living. And when you do that, you'll\nfind OTHER things that make you happy!
I don't WANT to be happy in this life!\nI want to be reunited with HER!
But if I die, that means her dream\nis going to die with me...
Say, is there any of that food left?
I'll be able to think about this more\nclearly once I'm feeling better.
Great idea! And while you eat,\nI'm gonna run and get Cleo.
I still cannot guarantee he will live,\nbut the fact he chose to eat is a\nrather positive sign.
Can't imagine much worse than losin'\nthe woman ya love. He's in for a long,\nhard road no matter how ya slice it.
Maybe it ain't our call to persuade\nthe guy one way or the other.
His desire to be reunited with his love\nis at least...understandable.
No, he has to LIVE! What's the point of\nlife if you just toss it aside when it's hard?
The thought of surrendering on life and\ndying all sad and alone is just...awful.
Even the saddest life has plenty of\nhappy moments in it, and it would\nbe totally wrong to forget that!
So yeah, maybe this is selfish,\nbut I still want to encourage him.
Because I believe good things will happen\nso long as you're alive to see them.
That is a lovely thought, Emma.
I was told to devote my energy to\nencouraging new people I meet.
And that's exactly what I'm gonna do.
He'll choose to live, and it's gonna be\nthe best choice he ever made.
